A dependency that a given type has on some other qualified type.

  • Constructor Details

    • Dependency

      public Dependency(Assignability a, List<? extends org.microbean.qualifier.NamedAttributeMap<?>> attributes, boolean box, VariableElement e)
      Creates a new Dependency.
      Parameters:
      a - an Assignability; may be null in which case a default Assignability will be used instead
      attributes - a List of NamedAttributeMaps; must not be null
      box - whether or not to box primitive types
      e - a VariableElement whose kind property is FIELD or PARAMETER; must not be null
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if e's kind property is neither FIELD nor PARAMETER
      NullPointerException - if attributes or e is null

    • Dependency

      public Dependency(BeanSelectionCriteria bsc)
      Creates a new Dependency.
      Parameters:
      bsc - a BeanSelectionCriteria; must not be null
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if bsc is null
      See Also:
      • Dependency(BeanSelectionCriteria, VariableElement)

    • Dependency

      public Dependency(BeanSelectionCriteria bsc, VariableElement e)
      Creates a new Dependency.
      Parameters:
      bsc - a BeanSelectionCriteria; must not be null; its type property will be ignored in favor of the type encapsulated by the supplied VariableElement argument instead, if that argument is non-null
      e - a VariableElement representing a field or executable parameter; may be null; if non- null, must have a kind property whose value is either FIELD or PARAMETER
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if e is non-null and e's kind property is neither FIELD nor PARAMETER
      NullPointerException - if bsc is null
